content.detailedDescription: I was locking up my truck and looked into the sky and noticed an orange light almost like a plane heading north to south. it stood out to me with the object being hazy, moving faster than a plane, and no flashing lights. it seemed like the objects had some lights on the front of it and was moving over twice the speed of an airplane at that altitude. i stood there watching it to see if it was a plane for about three minutes then it all of a sudden split into two and rocketed away from each other going east and west at a high rate of speed. after it split, it was no longer visible. i remained looking in the general vicinity for another minute to see if it would appear, but the objects never reappeared.
content.summary: Flying then split into two.

content.detailedDescription: Going to work and at 2:54am on new years day morning, i had just left the house and saw 4 bright orange lights what looked to be about 40 degrees 5 miles away in the very clear sky. i am 44yrs old, amateur astronomer for decades-own an 8" and 15" reflector telescope that i ground, polished, figured and built myself i share this info to give me some sort of credibility in my sky observation ability's. the bight orange lights were silent(jet sound/helicopter) lights were hovering toward another till one by one they diminished in size as if they were traveling away from me. flares/fireworks out of the question. this was truly my first experience with ufos. my first thoughts were flares but ruled that out fairly quickly after the motions were being controlled. well that's all i got. thank you.
content.summary: Bright orange starlike but much brighter, floating into formation and then what seemed like they left one at a time away from me as the their magnitude dropped away.

content.detailedDescription: i spotted this small / distant iridescent sphere whilst standing in my garden. (i have an open garden surrounded by nearby open countryside, with a great view of the sky.). i live alone and pop out into the garden to look for interesting objects several times every night. this glittering star like object immediately caught my eye because it was out of place. it was low, over the neighbouring rooftops at about 40-45 degrees  altitude. the sky was clear without any visible cloud cover. as i watched i realised that it was moving slowly and steadily in a southerly direction, thus no planet or star !! i watched for a minute or so and then took a chance by running in to grab my bino`s, which were directly behind the door. to my relief it was still there and visible when i returned.The bino`s made it even harder to focus. it was just like a spherical mass of random swirling colours.It then faded out as they often do. given the low positioning in the sky the fading out could possibly be attributed to a low cloud bank ?? i live directly under a major u.K. flightpath ( including nearby manchester airport ). i know all civilian and military aicraft, frequently watch and i.D. visible satellites on my phone and am familiar with the celestial constellations. i regularly visit military airshows , am 59 years of age and used to be a member of the local ( now folded ) u.F.O. club. this was just the kind of thing i hope to see when i go out into my garden all year round. it was something very unusual !!
content.summary: This object glittered ( like venus, but wrong time of day and moved), bright random colours. moved left to right.Faded out.

content.detailedDescription: New years 12:25ish am, kaunakakai hi.  right after the neighborhood finished the 20 min long firework show in ranch camp.  i was alerted by my father to "go look out in the sky what the f#@$ is that?"  i was followed outside by my mother to the south side of the house.  we witnessed a bright red-orange object floating east bound approx. 500-1000 ft off the ocean.  it did not have any blinking lights and was just a steady brilliant glow. my father and i both agree it was probably doing less than 100mph. my mother and father are both skeptics when it comes to such things yet neither of them could process a skeptics response to what we were seeing.  it continued on a eastern path for maybe 1min, then slowly turned south for 30 secs or so then slowly vanished.  i was able to get some crappy cell video of it.. i'm sure dozens of people had to have seen it as everyone was still bringing in the new year.
content.summary: Three people observed a unidentifiable object floating across the sky then disapearing

content.detailedDescription: At a bombfire in malabar, florida with 3 other people, i always skywatch, it was a full moon, i saw an orange object, kind of large for a meteor, i yelled for everyone to look, it headed toward earth, heading into atmosphere it slowed, fraught the atmosphere, moved right, then left, then backwards, all the while getting smaller, it again moved left and seemed to either flame out or reversed out of the atmosphere. it lasted about 1 minute and 50 seconds. we all were amazed, trying to understand the way it was moving and wondering what logical answer would there be for that kind of decisive movement. when it finally disappeared i started to go online to see if there were any other sightings.
content.summary: Falling down, large orange glow, fought gravity, moved l&r, up, down, then burned out

content.detailedDescription: I went outside on my back porch to smoke and read my novel. my porch is screened in. while reading, i just happened to glance up and i saw an unusual, orange-yellow light that appeared to be moving. i stepped out of the screened-in porch to get a better view. the light was definitely moving across the sky and appeared to flicker, becoming brighter than softer a few times before fading and than going out. when this light faded, i saw an object. it was dark outside and this "thing" was pretty far away but it appeared to be spherical in shape, was dark grey or black in color and seemed to move effortlessly. it made no noise that i could discern and had no other lights on or around it. truthfully, i thought this object may have been a helicopter at first, but when the light faded and i saw the object against the sky, i really had no idea what it could have been. now, this happened today, which is new year's eve. and, yes there were fire works around. but i know fireworks. they do not fly above your house and disappear over the horizon. this thing was not a firework. it was unlike anything i have ever seen before and did scare me for a moment, especially after its light faded out and i could still see "it" moving along the sky, silently. after the light faded, i could only track it for a second or two as it moved toward the horizon. i lost track of it due to it being so dark outside and the object habing no color or other lights on or around it. after it vanished, i stood for a moment to collect myself, went back in the screened porch and sat down for a few minutes to try and think, asking myself, did i really see what i just saw? this can't be happening to me. but it did. and i know what i saw was there and was real and that i do not know what it was.
content.summary: Strange light at night. no sound, light faded and could see an object before disappearing altogether.

content.detailedDescription: I was taking a walk in my neighbourhood on october 31st 2016 with my dog. i live in a neighbourhood that's very small and there is a lot of space between the houses. behind all the houses are a couple farms and then a valley. there is next to no light pollution in this valley or my neighbourhood. as i reached one of the largest gaps between houses in that neighbourhood, i saw a big glowing red orb of light. i didn't panic, i simply stood still and observed. the orb was slowly moving across the sky. i want to say it was headed west, but i am unsure. so it moved slowly for about 10 maybe 15 seconds. then it stopped and remained still for maybe a solid 5 minutes. it felt like an eternity, so i will say five instead of 10 because it did feel like 10. i continued observing it when suddenly it flew spontaneously in the complete opposite direction and was gone within an instant. it was lightning fast. i just continued with my walk and tried to process what i had just witnessed. it was a very interesting event.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: I was taking a walk and observed a bright red orb moving slowly across the sky, it stopped, remained still for a period of time and then took off in the opposite direction

content.detailedDescription: I was outside with my neighbor in our front yard balcony and we were watching the sky for the scheduled passing of the iss. before the space station was scheduled to come from the west to the east we were watching the stars. a white dot that we thought was a star suddenly moved from the s.W in the sky to the n.W. and stopped dead in the sky. my neighbor and i looked at each other and he asked me if that's the station and i said no. we both got creeped out but kept watching and when the station came at 901 as scheduled i said that's the station and about 3 minutes after the station passed overhead we noticed the same white dot move off slowly to the n.W and then faded out as it moved. this has happened couple of times during the last few times i have waited to see the iss go by but only from the west to east flight path.
content.summary: Mistook it for a star until it moved and stopped dead

content.detailedDescription: Strange things have happened to me since i was diagnosed with cancer at age 8. but this specific night something happened extremely close and i’ve tried to figure it out and i just can not. i was on the phone with my mother standing outside on my porch. i saw something right in front on me and even told my mother that i thought i just saw a shooting start or something. i brushed it off and went inside and started thinking about what i had seen and at what level it happened. i went back outside to retrace what had happened. i know the object i saw looked like a bright fireball and when it got to the power line or tree (i couldn’t tell until the next morning) i knew it had either vanished out of thin air or hit something and dissipated. i played it over and over in my mind that night and looked up what it could have been but nothing explained what i saw. i really thought it had hit the power line. but then i noticed a chunk out of the tree at the same level the fireball was. i do not know if it hit the tree or if the chunk out of the tree is from the fireball or if it hit the power line but i know it hit something and vanished. there is much more i could say but i’m going to leave it at this for now.
content.summary: Fireball at mid tree level then disintegrated ...

content.detailedDescription: I was in the the hotel el peten in flores sitting at the balcony and watching birds just before coming heavy rain and thunder storm. my wife first noticed the object coming across the lake (in front of the hotel) around 500 metres over ground. it was no plane, no helicopter, no baloon or comparable.It was a green disc situated in the air with a 45° angle, flying abruptedly forward, standing, flying again. i took my camera mounted a lens with 300mm focal length and began to shot pictures. the object crosses the lake and vanished abruptly in the north. because i had seen and taken pictures of several ufos in my life i was not extremely surprised but happy to see one again.
content.summary: Green disc (see picture), flying-standing-flying above ground

content.summary: Triangle shaped, moved quickly, verified by another person

content.detailedDescription: I left my house to walk my dog on 12-30-2017 at 8:25pm walking west, i usually look to the sky's for meteor showers, shooting stars. i saw at about a 45 degree angle on the horizon between myself and south mountain to the west an unusually bright and large red light with two smaller white lights to either side forming a disc shape. i stopped and observed it moving to the east toward me, i decided to call my daughter to see if she could see from her location east of me a few miles (she couldn't) i then observed the object stop and hover in place then start moving south. i attempted to take video but was unable to open video mode only a time lapse photo was taken (will need to review). my dog was getting agitated and whining then the disc went from being large and visible to accelerating to the southwest at such a rate of speed it went to a pinpoint and gone. i'm retired air force and that was not an aircraft from this earth, i have never seen anything like it in my life before, truly amazing. my dog seems to be bit lethargic after getting home and i have a very bad headache, not sure what to make of that as of yet.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Sighted a disc shaped object with large red light in the center and 2 white lights to either side moving east toward me while walking my dog.
